node.text:
In my early twenties I was lucky enough to get on a @NOLSedu course. It had a big impact on my life direction at the time and inspired me in a way I had not found elsewhere. I eventually taught at NOLS for several years. I found teaching at NOLS to be deeply satisfying and I can’t say enough about the growth a student (young or old) can gain on one of their courses. I got to see it first hand. Now I am fortunate enough to sit on the board because I truly believe NOLS is an organization that helps people on their path to finding their greatest potential. #thetrailtosuccess

Link in bio to learn more.

node.text:
If you love this land, make a plan to vote. No matter your politics, this land is our common ground. @protectourwinters has made it simple to make your plan to vote this November with their new Make A Plan To Vote Tool where you can check your registration, request an absentee ballot, and much more. Link in bio. #CommonGround #MakeADamnPlan

Are you in?

node.text: I used to spend months roaming, climbing and shooting in the desert. A lot of my first published photos were from this area and many of my early images were of @highsteph. Great to reunite for an epic day of climbing after all these years. Also fun to pick up some of the day w @DJIGlobal's new #OSMOAction. Pretty impressive for such a compact camera. And of course, Steph is still an awesome rope gun and all around badass! Check it: http://bit.ly/OSMO_JC or hit the link in my bio. #sponsored.

node.text: Proud to be joining the @panerai family, a brand and watchmaker I have admired for years. Their history and focus on innovation, elegant design, durability and sustainable practices are all attributes I appreciate and stand by. Onward and upward. #sponsored

node.text:
Proud to announce my first custom watch collaboration with my longtime partner @Panerai.  For the last year I've been working closely with the Panerai team on a watch that reflects my connection with the mountains and deep appreciation for both craftsmanship and design. They did it right - the watch strap and packaging are made from entirely recycled PET plastic. #PaneraixJimmyChin

📸 by @chrisfigenshau
